I found in the code that the percentage calculation is only considering the difference of **_contentSize.height - _innerContainer->getContentSize().height** which is not correct.

**As is:**

```
void ScrollView::scrollToPercentVertical(float percent, float second, bool attenuated)
{
    float minY = _contentSize.height - _innerContainer->getContentSize().height;
    float h = - minY;
    startAutoScrollChildrenWithDestination(Vec2(_innerContainer->getPosition().x, minY + percent * h / 100.0f), second, attenuated);
}
```

**After fix:**

```
void ScrollView::scrollToPercentVertical(float percent, float second, bool attenuated)
{
    float minY = _contentSize.height - _innerContainer->getContentSize().height;
    float h = _innerContainer->getContentSize().height * percent / 100.0f;
    float y = MIN(0, minY + h);
    startAutoScrollChildrenWithDestination(Vec2(_innerContainer->getPosition().x, y), second, attenuated);
}

```

After fixing the code as above, the scrolling correclty positions where I am expecting it to.

